description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bank Housekeeper &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dilke Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary – Band 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week – Variable&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gloucestershire Health and Care NHS Trust is looking for a friendly, conscientious and motivated individual to join the Facilities Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of the role is to provide a cleaning and catering service within our Community Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service we provide operates shifts across all of the seven days a week. The successful candidate will be working throughout the hospital in non-patient and inpatient areas. We are looking for a person who can work as part of the team to maintain the high standards of cleanliness and to prepare safe and consistently high standards of food and beverages for patients in our care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This patient facing role requires candidates to have good communication skills. The successful candidate will require the ability to follow instructions and procedures via written, verbal and computer based methods of communication and preferably has previous experience in a similar role or environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A flexible approach towards the work will be required to meet the changing priorities of the workload, duties and department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal discussion and any enquires please contact Jane Jones, Facilities Manager on 0300 421 8589.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 9th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shortlisting date: 10th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
